16/08/2009
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Four Macedonian soldiers were slightly injured on Friday (August 14th) in a suicide bomb attack in Afghanistan, the Defence Ministry announced Saturday. The attack killed a total of seven people and injured another 100. Macedonia has 164 troops in Afghanistan as part of NATO's International Security Assistance Force. Of them, 148 are guarding the Alliance's headquarters in Kabul. (Xinhua, MIA, Makfax, A1 - 15/08/09)
